<title>USA: RESEARCH ALERT - Microsoft cut to hold.</title>
<headline>RESEARCH ALERT - Microsoft cut to hold.</headline>
<dateline>LOS ANGELES 1997-07-18</dateline>
<text>
<p>Pacific Crest Securities downgraded Microsoft Corp to hold from buy based on the share price's 50 percent run-up over the past three months, analyst Rob Owens said Friday.</p>
<p>-- Owens said price seemed &quot;a little excessive&quot; given expected fiscal 1998 revenues of $14 billion.</p>
<p>-- He still sees the stock as &quot;core holding&quot; for investors.</p>
<p>-- Microsoft was off 5-3/4 at 143-3/4 early Friday afternoon.</p>
